snippet.textDisplay:
My coffee routine is part Chris/Delany/Chaey/Rick and part Claire - I use a Chemex type vessel and drink my coffee with heated milk like Claire and weigh/measure my water/beans like the pourover crew. To answer Claire's question re: who has the presence of mind to weigh/measure before coffee, for me I love my morning cup of coffee so much that I want to get it right, and that powers me through any pre-coffee mental haze.

Also, I never knew Molly's coffee soda was a thing, but it makes an experience I had a few months ago make so much more sense. I ordered a cold brew at a fancy coffee shop, and I am pretty sure that was what they served me. It was not what I was expecting AT ALL, and to me tasted like a very strange iced tea. When I went back to the counter to tell them I thought they got my order wrong, their response was, "No, that's how we do our cold brew." Sure, doesn't everyone add lemon and seltzer to their cold brew? LOL!

snippet.textDisplay: FYI: pouring coffee into milk does taste 100x better. Rather than pouring milk/half 'n half into scalding hot coffee that burns on contact (which is that swirling milk spirals you see) pouring the coffee in second heats up the milk more gradually so it doesn't scald. I never noticed the taste of burnt milk in my coffee until I started doing it the other way.
snippet.textOriginal: FYI: pouring coffee into milk does taste 100x better.
